trans-unit.source:
\n

Provides functionality to split a string into text elements and to iterate through those text elements.

\n
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxxxxxx xx xxxxx x xxxxxx xxxx xxxx xxxxxxxx xxx xx xxxxxxx xxxxxxx xxxxx xxxx xxxxxxxx.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
\n

The value in a set operation is null.

\n
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxx xxxxx xx x xxx xxxxxxxxx xx $xxxxxx$xxxx$$xxxxxx$.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
\n

Gets the first text element in a specified string.

\n
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxxx xxx xxxxx xxxx xxxxxxx xx x xxxxxxxxx xxxxxx.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
\n

The string from which to get the text element.
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxx xxxxxx xxxx xxxxx xx xxx xxx xxxx xxxxxxx.

trans-unit.source:
\n

A string containing the first text element in the specified string.

\n
trans-unit.target: $x$x$X xxxxxx xxxxxxxxxx xxx xxxxx xxxx xxxxxxx xx xxx xxxxxxxxx xxxxxx.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
\n

Gets the text element at the specified index of the specified string.

\n
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxxx xxx xxxx xxxxxxx xx xxx xxxxxxxxx xxxxx xx xxx xxxxxxxxx xxxxxx.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
\n

The string from which to get the text element.
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxx xxxxxx xxxx xxxxx xx xxx xxx xxxx xxxxxxx.

trans-unit.source:
\n

The zero-based index at which the text element starts.
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxx xxxx$xxxxx xxxxx xx xxxxx xxx xxxx xxxxxxx xxxxxx.

trans-unit.source:
\n

A string containing the text element at the specified index of the specified string.

\n
trans-unit.target: $x$x$X xxxxxx xxxxxxxxxx xxx xxxx xxxxxxx xx xxx xxxxxxxxx xxxxx xx xxx xxxxxxxxx xxxxxx.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
\n

\nindex is outside the range of valid indexes for str.
trans-unit.target: $x$x$$x$xx$xxxxx$$xx$ xx xxxxxxx xxx xxxxx xx xxxxx xxxxxxx xxx $xx$xxx$$xx$.

trans-unit.source:
\n

Returns an enumerator that iterates through the text elements of the entire string.

\n
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxxxxxx xx xxxxxxxxxx xxxx xxxxxxxx xxxxxxx xxx xxxx xxxxxxxx xx xxx xxxxxx xxxxxx.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
\n

Returns an enumerator that iterates through the text elements of the string, starting at the specified index.

\n
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxxxxxx xx xxxxxxxxxx xxxx xxxxxxxx xxxxxxx xxx xxxx xxxxxxxx xx xxx xxxxxx$ xxxxxxxx xx xxx xxxxxxxxx xxxxx.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
\n

The zero-based index at which to start iterating.
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxx xxxx$xxxxx xxxxx xx xxxxx xx xxxxx xxxxxxxxx.

trans-unit.source:
\n

\nindex is outside the range of valid indexes for str.
trans-unit.target: $x$x$$x$xx$xxxxx$$xx$ xx xxxxxxx xxx xxxxx xx xxxxx xxxxxxx xxx $xx$xxx$$xx$.

trans-unit.source:
\n

Returns the indexes of each base character, high surrogate, or control character within the specified string.

\n
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxxxxxx xxx xxxxxxx xx xxxx xxxx xxxxxxxxx$ xxxx xxxxxxxxx$ xx xxxxxxx xxxxxxxxx xxxxxx xxx xxxxxxxxx xxxxxx.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
\n

An array of integers that contains the zero-based indexes of each base character, high surrogate, or control character within the specified string.

\n
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xx xxxxx xx xxxxxxxx xxxx xxxxxxxx xxx xxxx$xxxxx xxxxxxx xx xxxx xxxx xxxxxxxxx$ xxxx xxxxxxxxx$ xx xxxxxxx xxxxxxxxx xxxxxx xxx xxxxxxxxx xxxxxx.$$x$$x
